WEBVTT

00:01.483 --> 00:02.700
<i>So here's what
you missed on Glee:</i>

00:02.784 --> 00:04.151
<i>Sue's pregnant,
which is crazy...</i>

00:04.202 --> 00:05.903
I had my eggs frozen
in the late '70s.

00:05.987 --> 00:06.853
<i>...and she won't say
who the father is,</i>

00:06.905 --> 00:08.372
<i>but insists that he's famous.</i>

00:08.456 --> 00:09.957
<i>Rachel and Finn
decided to get married</i>

00:10.024 --> 00:11.542
<i>after Regionals,
where the New Directions</i>

00:11.626 --> 00:13.494
<i>beat Sebastian and the Warblers
and a madrigal group</i>

00:13.545 --> 00:15.329
<i>that just sort of made
everyone uncomfortable.</i>

00:15.380 --> 00:17.081
<i>And Sebastian made up with
Blaine after he realized</i>

00:17.165 --> 00:18.699
<i>life's too short to blind
people with rock salt.</i>

00:18.750 --> 00:20.467
<i>Quinn thought Rachel and Finn
were too young to get married,</i>

00:20.535 --> 00:21.886
<i>and refused to go
to the wedding.</i>

00:21.970 --> 00:23.837
...which makes me really sad,
because I would have loved

00:23.889 --> 00:25.639
to have seen you in
a bridesmaid's dress, Quinn.

00:25.707 --> 00:27.474
<i>...but then changed her mind
and started texting</i>

00:27.542 --> 00:28.392
<i>while she raced
to the courthouse,</i>

00:28.476 --> 00:29.894
<i>and her car got hit by a truck.</i>

00:29.978 --> 00:30.811
<i>And that's what
you missed on Glee!</i>

00:34.683 --> 00:36.016
(school bell ringing)

00:36.067 --> 00:37.651
So do you think if Quinn
hadn't gotten into her accident,

00:37.719 --> 00:39.853
we still would've gone
through with the wedding?
Yeah, totally.

00:39.905 --> 00:41.722
Totally. I mean,
I'm kind of glad we're waiting.

00:41.773 --> 00:44.158
Now it doesn't have to be
a Justice of the Peace quickie.

00:44.225 --> 00:45.776
Hey, I was thinking
since Nationals

00:45.860 --> 00:47.695
are in Chicago this year,

00:47.746 --> 00:49.697
we-we should have the wedding
someplace special.

00:49.748 --> 00:52.116
Like-like on the pitcher's mound
of Wrigley Field.

00:52.200 --> 00:54.335
O-Or someplace else.
It's not that, it's Quinn.

00:54.402 --> 00:56.203
I can't stop thinking
about her. She's...

00:56.254 --> 00:58.589
Right behind you.

01:05.129 --> 01:07.298
Hi, Quinn!
We missed you so much.

01:07.382 --> 01:09.466
No, don't.

01:09.551 --> 01:12.186
I could have easily become one
of those creepy memorial pages

01:12.253 --> 01:14.972
in the yearbook, but by
the grace of God, I'm here.

01:16.975 --> 01:18.859
Believe it or not...

01:18.926 --> 01:20.477
this is the happiest
day of my life.

01:22.030 --> 01:24.031
Come on, Artie.
I'll race you to the choir room.

01:24.098 --> 01:25.816
(Elton John's
"I'm Still Standing" begins)

